And on your second question:

I believe I can super easily convert C++ code to MQL5 code, right?

Mostly yes, but with an important caveat.

MQL5 is essentially:

C++-like syntax
+
MetaTrader runtime
+
Trading API
+
Indicator API

So things like:

double EMA(...)
double ATR(...)
bool EntrySignal(...)

translate almost 1:1.

But:

OrderSend()
PositionSelect()
CopyRates()
iATR()

are MT5-specific.

